records.addlTxt:
Defendant in custody.
NO CONTEST plea entered to count 1, fail to support.  Convicted.
The State moves to dismiss and read in counts 2 through 5.  Motion granted.
Sentence is withheld and the defendant is placed on probation to DOC for two (2) years, consecutive to the prison sentence presently being served on count 1 of 16 CF 259, to commence upon defendant's discharge date after extended supervision ends.
Conditions of probation:
1) pay court costs;
2) pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC;
3) assessment, treatment, counseling as deemed appropriate by the Department's assessment process;
4) maintain fulltime employment or work search;
5) defendant is to comply with all child support orders and pay current and past support as ordered.
Minutes.
